					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In my last game, I used parallax scrolling as some little visual detail that is rarely used in other games.<br /><br />For my next game, which is a screen-by-screen-scrolling, top-down game, what visual details could you suggest that I might include?<br /><br />One thing that I already have in mind is to use the intensify bits:<br />In three parts of the game, the screen will be overlaid with red, green and blue respectively which will have a plot- or location-based justification.<br /><br />But I'm thinking of also using other visual tricks that you don't see very often in games.<br />Do you have any suggestions which techniques I could use?</div>

					
